nificantly greater, which underscores the importance of\nmolecular structure. Transport efficiencies of the biological motors studied\nhere are semi-optimized under the cellular condition ([ATP] $\\approx 1$ mM,\n$f=0-1$ pN). Our study indicates that among many possible directions of\noptimization, cytoskeletal motors are designed to operate at a high speed with\na minimal error while leveraging their energy resources.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Oct 2017 10:27:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 17 Oct 2017 04:45:18 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 23 Nov 2017 10:18:32 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 6 Jun 2019 03:15:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-07"}
