-validation, and application of the heat flux method is presented. The\nmethod is applied to a range of DIII-D discharges and finds a broadening factor\nof the deposition profile width which scales linearly with edge density\nfluctuation level. These experimental results are found to be consistent with\nthe full-wave beam broadening measured by the 3D full wave simulations in the\nsame discharges.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Oct 2017 10:45:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-10-11"}
